sentences: Kacem Kefi (Arabic: قاسم كافي) (August 5, 1945 – November 15, 2018) was a Tunisian singer and composer.
Kefi was self-taught in music, and released a pop song in the early 1970s to jumpstart his career.
Kefi also gave performances in Tel Aviv.
After his son's death in 2012, Kefi rarely produced new music.
